  "text": "More recently, the area under the dose curve (AUC) measurement attempts to combine reactivity and sensitivity into one (Fig. 2c) ; it is similar to a coordinate system of sensitivity and reactivity, but also incorporates partial anergy induced at high allergen concentrations and can be calculated even in cases where responses do not t well to a typical dose-response curve [CITATION_1] . ROC curves are used in identi cation of novel allergens when ≥ 7 sensitized patients are available.",
